EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
─────────────────
This audit covers the full Renderflow repository as of v0.2.1.  Two critical
release pipeline defects were identified and remediated as part of this audit
(see "Immediate Remediations" below).  The remaining findings are categorised
HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW and include a recommended fix and effort estimate for each.

Overall, Renderflow is architecturally sound with clean Rust idioms, a well-
designed graph engine, and a comprehensive release pipeline.  The primary
production risks are the previously broken release trigger and several gaps in
documentation and test coverage.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IMMEDIATE REMEDIATIONS (applied in this PR)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[FIX-1] Release workflow never triggered after version bump
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Root cause : GitHub Actions does not trigger other workflows when an event is
             created by GITHUB_TOKEN.  The bump-version workflow pushed the
             release tag using GITHUB_TOKEN, so release.yml was never triggered.
             This is a documented GitHub Actions security restriction preventing
             recursive workflow execution.

Fix applied:
  1. Added `workflow_dispatch` trigger to release.yml so it can be dispatched
     explicitly.
  2. Added `actions: write` permission and a "Dispatch release workflow" step to
     bump-version.yml that calls `gh workflow run release.yml --ref <tag>` after
     pushing the tag.  This bypasses the GITHUB_TOKEN restriction by converting
     the tag push into an explicit workflow dispatch.

Verification: The next `Bump Version` run will push the tag and then dispatch
the release pipeline.  Release artifacts, notes, and the GitHub Release entry
will be created automatically.

[FIX-2] README did not reflect current feature set
──────────────────────────────────────────────────
The README omitted:
  • The graph engine (DAG-based transform planner with petgraph)
  • Optimization modes (Speed / Quality / Balanced / Pareto)
  • Incremental build caching
  • AI transforms (Ollama / OpenAI backends with local cache)
  • CommandTransform (external command filter support)
  • Plugin system (runtime-registered PluginExecutor extensions)
  • Audio format conversion (40+ formats via FFmpeg)
  • Image format conversion (80+ formats via FFmpeg)
  • Updated release process documentation
  • Completed roadmap items

Fix applied: README.md rewritten to document all current features with examples,
architecture diagram, and accurate roadmap.

